text:
Jane Fonda received a special 80th birthday present too soon.

Before her next special day on December 21, the future octogenarian would go to her organization, the GCAPP fundraiser on Saturday night in Atlanta. The evening, called "Eight decades of Jane", was celebrated in honor of the famous founder's birthday.

With celebrity attendees such as actress Rosanna Arquette, musician Carole King and former husband of Fonda, Ted Turner invited guests made an offer during a live auction with articles like lunch with Fonda and her co-star Lily Tomlin and a visit to the set of Grace & Frankie as well as a dinner at the new house of the star in Los Angels
title: Jane Fonda celebrates her 80th birthday early by raising $ 1.3 million for charity – tech2.org
